========================
ENGLISH
========================

1. GENERAL RULES

- Parentheses must be attached:
  correct: input()
  wrong: input ()

- Blocks use {} with 2 spaces indentation:

If(condition) then {
  Console.display("ok")
}

- Case insensitive
- Comments start with #

---

2. TYPES

int → integer number
sel(max) → limited number
boolean → true or false
command → stores commands

Examples:
n1 = 10
Int n2 = 5
Sel(100) n3 = 50

---

3. VARIABLES

- Can be created with or without type:

n1 = 10
Int n2 = 5

- Names cannot contain spaces

---

4. OPERATORS

== equal
#= different
< less than
> greater than
+ addition
- subtraction
* multiplication
/ division

---

5. CONSOLE

Console.display(value)
→ prints to console

Console.input(text)
→ user input

Console.clear()
→ clears console

---

6. CLEARING (RENDER)

Console.back.backspace
→ removes 1 character

Console.back.enter
→ removes 1 line

back.line(line)
→ moves to specified line, discarding all saved states

back.linesave(line)
→ moves to specified line, keeping saved states

---

7. INPUT

Console.input("text")
value = _input

---

8. INPUT DETECT

key = input.detect()

Common values:
"w", "a", "s", "d"
"enter"
"space"
"escape"

---

9. CONVERSION

transform.int(expr)
transform.sel(max)(expr)

Example:
n1 = transform.int(Console.input())

---

10. REPLACE

Replace(var) to "value"

---

11. IF (NO ELSE)

JX does not have an ELSE command.

To simulate ELSE, use two conditions:

cond = (condition)

If(cond) then {
  true code
}

If(cond #= true) then {
  false code
}

---

12. LOOP

Loop {
  code
}

---

13. STOP

stop()
→ stops current loop

stop(var)
→ stops specific loop

---

14. WAIT

Wait(seconds)
Wait.frame(frames)

---

15. COMMAND STORAGE

cmd = Console.display("hi")
cmd

---

16. EXAMPLE

Loop {
  key = input.detect()

  If(key == "w") then {
    Console.display("up")
  }

  Wait.frame(5)
}

---

